				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">^ Sure. But if you want to write to vram during active display with Txx instructions, you have to use smaller segments like 32 bytes as not to delay hsync interrupts too long (all writes to vdc regs are buffered, but you have a 455 cpu cycle window to get them written per line). That brings down the transfer rate to vram at 7.5 cycles per byte during active display (all VDC reg access have +1 cycle penalty to read/write instructions), and 6.5 cycles for non VDC/VCE areas of memory.<br /><br /> If you embedded graphics as ST1/ST2 opcodes, its 5 cycles a byte to vram and is interruptible.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />__________________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://pcedev.wordpress.com">http://pcedev.wordpress.com</a><!-- m --></div>
