						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">MVP/MVN on the 65816 are slower, at 7 cycles per byte, and those cycles are on average more than twice as long as HuC6280 cycles. But MVP/MVN can be interrupted.</div><br />Hu6280's TXX are also more powerful, because there are not limited to RAM/ROM only,you can use them for transfer through a 8/16 bits port.</div>

