						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">&gt; you have to use smaller segments like 32 bytes as not to delay hsync interrupts too long<br /><br />The PCE VDC supports Hsync interrupts? Where and how? I only saw six VDC interrupt request types: sprite collision, sprite overflow, line coincidence, Vblank, VRAM DMA end, SATB DMA end.</div><br />Yes it's the bit 2 of the VDC status(if HSYNC interrupt is not disabled ,bit 2 of VDC register $5) .<br />You can set the line you want to have an interrupt with the VDC register $6 and you must add 64 to your line for the proprer VDC line interrupt(because the VDC start to draw the screen at line 64 and not 0)  .<br />Of course you can set multiple line interrupt in a single frame(but one line at a time) .<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Just a guess, but perhaps tomaitheous was referring to line coincidence</div><br />Yes it seems to be as byuu has interpreted.<br /><br />request types: sprite collision(bit 0), sprite overflow(bit 1), <strong>line coincidence(bit 2)</strong>, Vblank(bit 5), VRAM DMA end(bit 4), SATB DMA end(bit 3).<br /><br />But it's simply called scanline interrupt flag and not line coincidence.</div>

