				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">byuu sorry to not have been more precise  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarassed" /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">64 is not the 64th scanline. It's the first visible scanline (however that is defined).</div><br />Fortunately tomaitheous explained it with more details .<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I've never emulated a system that has the equivalent of setting your own Xorg modelines before.</div><br /> <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> <br />yes i agree, it's a little bit confusing, but permit a large screen configurations like wide screen/letter box without any tricks  .<br />The cool thing is with the SGX, you can configure each VDC with your own set of screen parameters .</div>

